OL,3,CPolitician suspended for 28 days
OL,4,Cwithout pay over conduct breaches
OL,6,FA longstanding Jersey politician has
OL,7,Fbeen suspended for 28 days without pay
OL,8,Fafter breaching the States' Code of
OL,9,FConduct multiple times.
OL,11,FDeputy Philip Ozouf's colleagues voted
OL,12,F29-17 in favour of suspending him,
OL,13,Fwith three abstentions.
OL,15,FThe temporary ban, proposed by the
OL,16,FPrivileges and Procedures Committee
OL,17,F(PPC), comes into force immediately,
OL,18,Fmeaning Deputy Ozouf will not take
OL,19,Fpart in the rest of this week's
OL,20,FStates' debates.
