OL,6,FThe island's Commissioner for
OL,7,FStandards found he breached paragraphs
OL,8,Ftwo, three, four and five of the Code
OL,9,Fof Conduct, relating to his ability to
OL,10,Fuphold the law, adhere to the Seven
OL,11,FPrinciples of Public Life, act in the
OL,12,Fpublic interest above any private
OL,13,Finterests, and uphold public trust.
OL,15,FPoliticians were split on whether
OL,16,FDeputy Ozouf should be suspended after
OL,17,Fhe committed motoring offences late
OL,18,Flast year and failed to engage with
OL,19,Fthe investigation.
