OL,6,FDeputy Sir Philip Bailhache said
OL,7,Ftaking this action would be
OL,8,F"disproportionate and unfair", whilst
OL,9,Fsetting a concerning precedent.
OL,11,FConversely, Deputy Lyndsay Feltham
OL,12,Flaid out Reform Jersey's position,
OL,13,Farguing that Deputy Ozouf had brought
OL,14,Fthe Assembly "into disrepute" by
OL,15,F"failing to follow due process and
OL,16,Fbreaking the law".
OL,18,FDeputy Ozouf was caught driving 31mph
OL,19,Fin a 15mph zone without displaying
OL,20,Fvalid car insurance in November last
OL,21,Fyear.
